                 who="http://papyri.info/editor/users/costasbala">Commit - I've integrated BL 7 and  BL 11 corrections. Furthermore, in lin7 I've corrected ἀ̣π̣ὸ̣ [χωρ]ί̣[ο]υ̣ =&gt; ἀ̣π̣[ο κώ]μ̣η̣ς. The final sigma is clear, χωρίου as a term would be too early for the village. The latest (for now) attestation of it as κώμη was P.Neph. 32.5 (344). In consequence, this puts into doubt the restoration in the lacuna of χωρίου in SB 18.13260.7/21 (328). </change>
